'''Pacific Southwest Chapter of the National Television Academy''' is a division of the [[National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences]]. The [[San Diego, California]] division was founded in 1972. In addition to granting [[Emmy Awards]] for the Pacific Southwest region, this division awards scholarships, honors industry veterans at the Silver Circle Celebration, conducts National [[Student television station|Student Television]] Awards of Excellence, has a free research and a nationwide job bank. The chapter also participates in judging Emmy entries at the regional and national levels.<ref name="urlNational Academy of Television Arts and Sciences, Pacific Southwest Chapter">{{cite web |url=http://www.nataspsw.org/scholarships.asp |title=National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences, Pacific Southwest Chapter |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher=[[NATAS]] |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-10}}Academy History</ref>
==Boundaries==
The academy is divided into the following boundaries and encompasses the Pacific areas of [[California]] which includes, [[San Diego]], [[Bakersfield]], [[Palm Springs]], [[San Luis Obispo]], [[Santa Maria, California|Santa Maria]], [[Santa Barbara, California|Santa Barbara]] and [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]. These boundaries are responsible for the submission of television broadcast materials presented for awards considerations.<ref name="urlNational Academy of Television Arts and Sciences, Pacific Southwest Chapter">{{cite web |url=http://www.nataspsw.org/home.asp |title=National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences, Pacific Southwest Chapter |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher=[[NATAS]] |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-10}}Boundaries</ref>
